'''Tripwires''' are traps, that can be found around the [[Isafdar]] forest in [[Tirannwn]]. They trigger four surrounding crossbows camouflaged as '''Twigs'''. Unsuccessful attempts to pass them will deal 10 damage and [[poison]] the player starting at 2. The player can click Step-over on the tripwire to attempt to pass them, but they can be walked or ran across if the player is willing to take the damage.
[[File:Twigs (trap).png|thumb|left|200px|Twigs, camouflaged crossbows triggered by the tripwire.]]

==Success chance==
The success chance of passing this trap ranges linearly from 30/255 at level 1 Agility to 155/255 at level 99 Agility.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Kieren|url=https://twitter.com/JagexKieren/status/720154872079888384|date=13 April 2016|archiveurl=https://archive.is/2v2o8|archivedate=30 May 2020|quote=So you know that nightmarishly difficult to click tripwire in the Elven lands? Here are the odds of failing it... [https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Cf6BCc8WwAAmIgE.jpg]}}

